Seplat Petroleum Development Plc. has reappointed Ifueko Marina Omoigui-Okauru as its independent director. The company’s shareholders according to a statement from the oil firm, unanimously approved her reappointment during the company’s Annual General Meeting (AGM). The company explained that Omoigui-Okauru had been an independent non-executive director at Seplat Petroleum Development Company Plc since March, 2013. She obtained a Master of Science in management science from Imperial College, University of London in 1986 and a Bachelor of Science in accounting from the University of Lagos in 1983. She has held several positions within the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS), including appointments as the first female executive chairman of the FIRS, and the first female chairman of the Joint Tax Board and member of the Nigerian President’s Economic Management Team charged with responsibility for tax reform in Nigeria.  She served as the managing partner of Compliance Professionals Plc. Omoigui-Okauru previously served as chief responsibility officer of ReStraL Limited from 1996 to 2004.